ved any previous network connections on these devices to the BYU-Idaho Wi-Fi, which in turn deletes any passwords associated with those connections.</p>
<p>In order to reconnect to the BYU-Idaho Wi-Fi and enter your new password on this device:</p>
<p>1. Go back to the "Settings" app and click Wi-Fi, you should be  given a list of available Wi-Fi networks to choose from.</p>
<p>2. Tap the "BYUI"  Network, and you will then be asked to put in your username and  password.</p>
<p>3. Type in your "my.byui" username with your new password.</p>
<p><img height="305px;" src="Images/helpdesk/iOS Wireless/iOS4.png" width="206px;" /><img height="303px;" src="Images/helpdesk/iOS Wireless/iOS5.png" width="203px;" /></p>
<ul>
<li>Note: If  the "BYUI" network doesn't appear in the "Choose a Network..." turn off  your Wi-Fi and then turn it back on, it should then show up. </li>
</ul>
